President Joe Biden spoke with President Mohamed bin Zayed of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) to reaffirm the strong relationship between the two countries. They also discussed the upcoming COP28 climate summit in Dubai, with President Biden asking Vice President Kamala Harris to attend on his behalf. The aim is to showcase US leadership on climate issues and encourage global action. The US delegation will include Special Presidential Envoy for Climate John Kerry and representatives from over 20 departments and agencies. The leaders also discussed the Middle East situation, welcoming recent progress in the hostage situation and humanitarian aid to Gaza. President Biden emphasized the US commitment to peace and security in the region.